00:00:22.000 --> 00:00:27.240
If you are not joining us live, you miss out on the amazing chat that's going on. So find

00:00:27.240 --> 00:00:30.719
the link in the description where you can add our call to your calendar and come hang

00:00:30.719 --> 00:00:35.680
out with the most supportive, friendly, and funny data community you'll ever experience.

00:00:35.680 --> 00:00:41.279
Can't wait to see you there. I am excited to introduce our featured leader today. We

00:00:41.279 --> 00:00:47.119
have Ryan Johnson. He is a data science advisor here at Posit with Rachel and Isabella and

00:00:47.119 --> 00:00:51.480
I. Ryan, it's so good to have you. It would be great if you could introduce yourself.

00:00:51.480 --> 00:00:55.000
Tell us a little bit about what you do and something you like to do for fun.

00:00:55.840 --> 00:01:01.360
Yeah, it's really great to be here. I think Rachel reached out to me on Tuesday to see

00:01:01.360 --> 00:01:06.959
if I'd be a part of this Data Science Hangout. No, no, I'm very pumped to be here. I've been

00:01:06.959 --> 00:01:11.639
kind of joining these off and on for the past couple of years. So it's just great to see

00:01:11.639 --> 00:01:17.040
you all again and to come speak and tell a little bit about my story. But for those I've

00:01:17.040 --> 00:01:21.800
not met, my name is Ryan Johnson. As Libby mentioned, my official title is a Data Science

00:01:21.800 --> 00:01:25.519
Advisor. I fully confess, I don't love that title that much.

00:01:25.879 --> 00:01:27.720
What would you prefer? Pick something else.

00:01:28.080 --> 00:01:34.519
That's the thing. I don't really know. There's certainly, you know, developer advocate has

00:01:34.519 --> 00:01:38.839
been something that I know Isabella is probably very familiar with. But it's not exactly what

00:01:38.839 --> 00:01:44.080
I do. So just kind of like this fuzzy area, which I'll probably talk more about, like

00:01:44.080 --> 00:01:49.320
why it's fuzzy in a little bit, because our team at Posit that I work on is actually really

00:01:49.320 --> 00:01:53.800
new. So that might kind of dictate how my title potentially changes over time.

00:01:53.800 --> 00:02:01.160
We're not really sure. But as a Data Science Advisor, on any given day at Posit, the bulk

00:02:01.160 --> 00:02:08.520
of my day is either creating content or delivering some type of workshop, webinar, demo,

00:02:09.119 --> 00:02:10.919
primarily for our professional customers.

00:02:10.919 --> 00:02:16.320
So the folks that are using like Posit Connect, Posit Workbench, Posit Package Manager, but

00:02:16.320 --> 00:02:20.160
also for teams that are also just trying to upskill on data science.

00:02:20.160 --> 00:02:25.600
So I teach a few like Intro to R, Intro to Python, Intro to Shiny, Renv, all those

00:02:25.600 --> 00:02:28.839
workshops that, you know, we've got a lot of requests over the years for a little bit

00:02:28.839 --> 00:02:31.600
more, you know, educational material.

00:02:31.600 --> 00:02:33.559
So that's what I do a lot on a day to day.

00:02:34.759 --> 00:02:40.360
I've been at Posit now for a little over six years, and when I first joined Posit, I was

00:02:40.360 --> 00:02:43.360
not in this field. I was actually in customer success.

00:02:43.399 --> 00:02:47.360
So there may be some folks here on the call, especially if you've been around the Posit

00:02:47.520 --> 00:02:52.160
world for a while, that maybe I was your customer success manager at some point.

00:02:53.479 --> 00:02:56.919
I know, you know, potentially folks maybe like the Pfizer, I know, joined there.

00:02:56.919 --> 00:03:02.039
I was at one point your customer success manager, but that's been many moons ago.

00:03:03.600 --> 00:03:08.880
But yeah, in addition to Posit stuff, it was like a little fun fact.

00:03:08.960 --> 00:03:10.119
My wife's in the military.

00:03:10.119 --> 00:03:13.960
So every couple of years we jump around and live somewhere else.

00:03:13.960 --> 00:03:16.199
And currently I reside in Lima, Peru.

00:03:17.440 --> 00:03:20.279
Lima, Peru is a really cool city.

