what do you think is the most common thing that people don't realize they can do?

00:49:25.393 --> 00:49:28.393
Yeah, like we have there's so many new features.

00:49:28.393 --> 00:49:32.393
It's so hard to like tell people everything that's possible.

00:49:32.393 --> 00:49:34.393
What's the most common one?

00:49:34.393 --> 00:49:40.393
And I'll preface this by saying like I am not a salesperson and my job is never to sell.

00:49:40.393 --> 00:49:42.393
And that's not what I'm going to do right now.

00:49:42.393 --> 00:49:44.393
So if anyone's like, oh, God, here we go.

00:49:44.393 --> 00:49:46.393
Ryan's going to try to sell me stuff.

00:49:46.393 --> 00:49:48.393
That is not what I'm going to do.

00:49:48.393 --> 00:49:53.393
But just to kind of explain, again, what I do on a day-to-day as a Posnit educator,

00:49:53.393 --> 00:49:58.393
it is primarily like showing teams how to get the most value out of our professional tools.

00:49:58.393 --> 00:50:04.393
If you've never heard of the tool Posnit Workbench before, and let's say I was just like, here.

00:50:04.393 --> 00:50:06.393
Here's Posnit Workbench.

00:50:06.393 --> 00:50:11.393
I guarantee you most of you all would be able to figure it out in a matter of seconds.

00:50:11.393 --> 00:50:16.393
Because all it's doing is taking all those IDEs that you already know and love, like RStudio,

00:50:16.393 --> 00:50:23.393
Positron, VS Code, JupyterLab, JupyterNotebook, and just bringing them to a more centralized location,

00:50:23.393 --> 00:50:26.393
like on a server that your administrators can manage.

00:50:26.393 --> 00:50:30.393
So everyone here who does data science, you'll feel right at home with Posnit Workbench.

00:50:30.393 --> 00:50:34.393
There's not a big learning curve with getting started with Workbench.

00:50:34.393 --> 00:50:39.393
But for my workshops, typically the thing that people don't know going into it,

00:50:39.393 --> 00:50:44.393
and I try to really emphasize, is the value of Posnit Connect.

00:50:44.393 --> 00:50:48.393
Because oftentimes if you've never heard of or used Posnit Connect before,

00:50:48.393 --> 00:50:51.393
that is the tool that's going to be the most new.

00:50:51.393 --> 00:50:55.393
And if you've never heard of it before, let's imagine you've created a Shiny application

00:50:55.393 --> 00:51:00.393
that you're really proud of, and you want to share it with somebody else.

00:51:00.393 --> 00:51:02.393
Sometimes that's pushing it to version control.

00:51:02.393 --> 00:51:04.393
That person pulls it into their computer.

00:51:04.393 --> 00:51:09.393
They may have to do some j-rigging to make sure all the packages match versions

00:51:09.393 --> 00:51:11.393
in the right R version in order to get it to work.

00:51:11.393 --> 00:51:15.393
That may be fine if you're a good, solid R Python developer.

00:51:15.393 --> 00:51:19.393
But if you're not a developer, like maybe your boss or a family member,

00:51:19.393 --> 00:51:24.393
really wants to see this application you developed, that's where Connect comes into play.

00:51:24.393 --> 00:51:29.393
Its whole purpose is to make sharing of any open source insight you developed

00:51:29.393 --> 00:51:31.393
as easy as possible.

00:51:31.393 --> 00:51:34.393
Essentially, you can share content like you would share any other website.

00:51:34.393 --> 00:51:39.393
You can just grab a URL for some content on Connect and share it with somebody else.

00:51:39.393 --> 00:51:42.393
And you get a lot of control over who can see and access that,

00:51:42.393 --> 00:51:47.393
especially for teams that have big security concerns of being able to share content.

00:51:47.393 --> 00:51:50.393
So that's a lot of my workshops.

00:51:50.393 --> 00:51:53.393
Oftentimes that is the main thing I'm trying to demonstrate,

00:51:53.393 --> 00:51:57.393
is how to publish to Connect and how to share it with other people.

00:51:57.393 --> 00:52:03.393
Because that is often the newest things for folks that have never used Connect before.

00:52:03.393 --> 00:52:04.393
Fantastic.

