00:53:17.393 --> 00:53:20.393
so that's another reason to get a Ph.D.

00:53:20.393 --> 00:53:25.393
But the things you learn in a Ph.D. do apply to anything.

00:53:25.393 --> 00:53:28.393
That is something that I definitely want to emphasize.

00:53:28.393 --> 00:53:33.393
I guess if there's going to be career advice here for anyone that's kind of on the,

00:53:33.393 --> 00:53:36.393
not sure if you want to do a Ph.D. or not a Ph.D.

00:53:36.393 --> 00:53:42.393
Critical thinking is a very fundamental skill that will get you very far in a lot of different things.

00:53:42.393 --> 00:53:48.393
That's something that a Ph.D. is, that's the main goal, is to teach you how to critically think about problems.

00:53:48.393 --> 00:53:54.393
And these are problems, again, that are not limited to just the field that you're getting a Ph.D. in.

00:53:54.393 --> 00:53:58.393
So, like, if that's what you enjoy, if you enjoy, like, problem solving,

00:53:58.393 --> 00:54:04.393
and you wanted to just, like, test that to the max, a Ph.D. could be a really good fit for you.

00:54:04.393 --> 00:54:09.393
But if you're trying to just get a Ph.D. just to get the letters after your name,

00:54:10.393 --> 00:54:13.393
not always the best decision.

00:54:13.393 --> 00:54:17.393
And you just really got to think about, like, what's next after the Ph.D.?

00:54:17.393 --> 00:54:20.393
When I was going through my Ph.D., we had a very small class.

00:54:20.393 --> 00:54:23.393
I think it was only about five of us that graduated in my class.

00:54:23.393 --> 00:54:27.393
That's not typical, but Uniform Services University was very small.

00:54:27.393 --> 00:54:30.393
We had a few people drop out for a variety of reasons,

00:54:30.393 --> 00:54:34.393
but the primary one is they just didn't know what they were getting themselves into.

00:54:34.393 --> 00:54:39.393
So, I love this idea in the chat of, like, let's talk about it.

00:54:39.393 --> 00:54:44.393
Ph.D. scientists can talk about their experience so that the more informed you can get about, like,

00:54:44.393 --> 00:54:47.393
what does it mean getting a Ph.D. in various fields?

00:54:47.393 --> 00:54:51.393
I mean, I assume we're all going to be very in, like, sciences, data science,

00:54:51.393 --> 00:54:55.393
but there may be some folks you're going to call that want to do, like, philosophy or something like that,

00:54:55.393 --> 00:54:56.393
which is perfectly fine.

00:54:56.393 --> 00:54:59.393
But, again, it's still going to train you to think critically.

